---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import { site } from '../../config/site';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms of use for the Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame website and historical archive."
  canonicalPath="/terms/"
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'Terms of Use', path: '/terms/' }]}
>
  <div class="page-shell">
    <PageHero title="Terms of Use" intro="Terms for responsible use of the Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame website and historical archive." />
    <section class="section">
      <article class="page-surface prose terms-copy">
        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 26, 2026</p>

        <h2>Site purpose</h2>
        <p>JRHOF.org exists to share information about the Joe Rossi Umpires Hall of Fame, preserve historical records, recognize inductees, support Hall of Fame events, and provide ways for the community to contact and support the organization.</p>

        <h2>Organization</h2>
        <p>The site is published by {site.legalName} for the {site.name}. The organization’s EIN is {site.ein}.</p>

        <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>Please use the site respectfully and only for lawful, personal, educational, historical, or community purposes. Do not attempt to interfere with the site, submit false or harmful information, misuse forms, or use site content in a misleading way.</p>

        <h2>Historical and archive content</h2>
        <p>Biographies, names, dates, photographs, and event details are preserved from historical records and community sources. The organization works to present information accurately, but the archive may be incomplete, under review, or contain errors.</p>
        <p>If you have a documented correction, biography update, portrait concern, or historical material to share, use the <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a>. The organization may review submissions before making public changes.</p>

        <h2>Donations and payments</h2>
        <p>Online donations are processed by Stripe or another approved PCI-compliant payment processor. Do not submit payment card numbers through the contact form or email.</p>
        <p>Details specific to a donation, event, or sponsorship may be provided with the applicable payment or registration option. Contact the organization before completing a transaction if you have questions about those details.</p>

        <h2>Events</h2>
        <p>Event dates, locations, prices, registration details, and availability may change. The organization will try to keep public event information current, but users should confirm details before making plans.</p>

        <h2>External links</h2>
        <p>The site may link to external websites or documents. External sites are not controlled by the organization, and their content, privacy practices, and availability may differ from JRHOF.org.</p>

        <h2>Intellectual property and content use</h2>
        <p>Site text, photographs, logos, documents, and archive materials may be owned by the organization, contributors, photographers, sponsors, or other rights holders. Do not copy, sell, alter, or republish site content in a way that misrepresents the Hall of Fame, the inductees, or the source material.</p>

        <h2>No guarantee</h2>
        <p>The site is provided as a public information and archive resource. The organization does not guarantee that all content is complete, error-free, continuously available, or suitable for every purpose.</p>

        <h2>Limitation of responsibility</h2>
        <p>To the extent allowed by applicable law, the organization is not responsible for losses or damages arising from use of the site, reliance on incomplete historical information, external links, or temporary site unavailability.</p>

        <h2>Questions</h2>
        <p>For questions, corrections, or concerns about these terms, use the <a href="/contact/">Contact page</a>.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .terms-copy { margin-inline: auto; }
</style>
